<step class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="C:\Users\sim\Dropbox (SIM University)\Leon\Backup\DITA\tasks\maintainstorage.dita" xtrc="step:2;24:7"><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="C:\Users\sim\Dropbox (SIM University)\Leon\Backup\DITA\tasks\maintainstorage.dita" xtrc="cmd:2;24:12">Every once in a while, shake your computer.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="C:\Users\sim\Dropbox (SIM University)\Leon\Backup\DITA\tasks\maintainstorage.dita" xtrc="info:1;24:67">This will
cause the bits to fall more comfortably in to place.</info></step>
<step class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="C:\Users\sim\Dropbox (SIM University)\Leon\Backup\DITA\tasks\maintainstorage.dita" xtrc="step:3;26:7"><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="C:\Users\sim\Dropbox (SIM University)\Leon\Backup\DITA\tasks\maintainstorage.dita" xtrc="cmd:3;26:12">Run Scandisk on the drive at least once a day.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="C:\Users\sim\Dropbox (SIM University)\Leon\Backup\DITA\tasks\maintainstorage.dita" xtrc="info:2;26:70">This
